# Versioning policy

## The rule

- Always use the **latest stable** version of every dependency.
- Pin **exact** versions in `package.json` (no `^`, `~`, or ranges).
- Renovate Bot auto-PRs minor + patch bumps; majors are reviewed manually.

## Before adding a new dependency

1. Run `npm view <pkg> version` to confirm latest stable.
2. Check it's actively maintained (last release < 12 months) and used widely (≥ 50k weekly downloads or backed by a known org).
3. Verify it's compatible with the rest of our stack (Node 22, React 19, ESM-first preferred).
4. If adding to `core/`, verify it's pure JS (no Node-only deps, no DOM-only deps).
5. Add an exact version to `package.json` like `"foo": "1.2.3"`.
6. Document why in the PR description (and update the relevant doc page).

## On a major upgrade

- Read the changelog.
- Confirm Renovate / Dependabot doesn't auto-merge it.
- Run full test suite locally.
- Test E2E happy paths.
- Update related code as needed.

## When checking versions in conversation

If you're not sure what the latest stable is, **search the web** before recommending a version. Don't rely on memory.

## Locked versions in code

The detailed list of intended versions lives in `docs/03-architecture/tech-stack.md`. That doc is updated when a major upgrade lands.

## Don't

- Don't pin to outdated majors "because that's what we used somewhere else."
- Don't use `latest` tag in `package.json`.
- Don't use beta / RC versions in production deps without an ADR.

See `docs/03-architecture/adr/0007-latest-stable-versioning-policy.md`.
